addExitQueue(uint256,address).details: the queue is created as a new contract instance.

enqueue(uint256,address,uint64,(uint256).details: emits ExitQueued event. The event can be used to back trace the priority inside the queue.Caller of this function should add "pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;" on top of file

params.exitId: Id for the exit processor contract to understand how to process such exit
params.exitProcessor: The exit processor contract that would be called during "processExits"
params.exitableAt: The earliest time that such exit can be processed
params.txPos: Transaction position for the exit priority. For SE it should be the exit tx, for IFE it should be the youngest input tx position.
params.vaultId: Vault id of the vault that stores exiting funds

enqueue(uint256,address,uint64,(uint256).return: a unique priority number computed for the exit

params._outputId: The output id to be flagged as spent

params.vaultId: Id of the vault that handles the token

hasExitQueue(uint256,address).return: bool represents whether the queue for a token was created.

initAuthority().details: Can be called only once, before any call to `submitBlock`.All block submission then needs to be send from msg.sender address.see discussion in https://github.com/omisego/plasma-contracts/issues/233

isExitGameSafeToUse(address).details: Exposes information about exit games quarantine

params._contract: address of the exit game contract

isExitGameSafeToUse(address).return: boolean whether the contract is safe to use and is not under quarantine.

params.maxExitsToProcess: maximal number of exits to process.
params.topExitId: unique priority of the first exit that should be processed. Set to zero to skip the check.
params.vaultId: vault id of the vault that stores exiting funds.

registerExitGame(uint256,address,uint8).details: emits ExitGameRegistered event to notify clients

params._contract: address of the exit game contract.
params._protocol: protocol of the transaction, 1 for MVP and 2 for MoreVP.
params._txType: tx type that the exit game want to register to.

registerVault(uint256,address).details: emits VaultRegistered event to notify clients

params._vaultId: the id for the vault contract to register.

params.newAuthority: address of new authority, cannot be blank.

submitBlock(bytes32).details: emit BlockSubmitted eventBlock number jumps 'childBlockInterval' per submission.see discussion in https://github.com/omisego/plasma-contracts/issues/233

params._blockRoot: Merkle root of the plasma block.

submitDepositBlock(bytes32).details: Block number adds 1 per submission, could have at most 'childBlockInterval' deposit blocks between two child chain blocks.

params._blockRoot: Merkle root of the plasma block.

addExitQueue(uint256,address).notice: Adds queue to the plasma framework.

batchFlagOutputsSpent(bytes32[]).notice: Batch flags outputs that are spent

enqueue(uint256,address,uint64,(uint256).notice: Enqueue exits from exit game contracts. This 'enqueue' function puts the exit into the        priority queue to enforce the priority of exit during 'processExits'.

exitGameToTxType(address).notice: public getter for getting tx type with exit game address

exitGames(uint256).notice: public getter for getting exit game address with tx type

flagOutputSpent(bytes32).notice: Flags a single output as spent

hasExitQueue(uint256,address).notice: Checks if queue for particular token was created.

initAuthority().notice: Sets the operator's authority address and unlocks block submission.

isAnyOutputsSpent(bytes32[]).notice: Checks if any of the output with the given outputIds is spent already.

isExitGameSafeToUse(address).notice: Checks whether the contract is safe to use and is not under quarantine

processExits(uint256,address,uint160,uin.notice: Processes any exits that have completed the challenge period. Exits would be processed according to the exit priority.

protocols(uint256).notice: public getter for getting protocol with tx type

registerExitGame(uint256,address,uint8).notice: Register an exit game within the PlasmaFramework. The function can only be called by the maintainer.

registerVault(uint256,address).notice: Register a vault within the PlasmaFramework. This can only be called by the maintainer.

setAuthority(address).notice: Allows the operator to set a new authority address. This allows to implement mechanical re-org protection mechanism, explained in https://github.com/omisego/plasma-contracts/issues/118

submitBlock(bytes32).notice: Allows the authority to submit the Merkle root of a plasma block.

vaultToId(address).notice: public getter for getting vault id with vault address

vaults(uint256).notice: public getter for getting vault address with vault id
